unit.question:
The steps Quentin took to evaluate the expression ${a}m - ${a} \div ${a} when m = ${b} are shown below.
${a}m - ${a} \div ${a}\ when\ m=${b}

${a} \times ${b} = ${c} 

${c} - ${a} = ${c-a} 

${c-a} \div ${a} = ${(c-a)/a} 


What should Quentin have done differently in order to evaluate the expression?
